and%20a%20dog%20barked.%20The%20unexpected%20noise%20made%20me%20jump%20and%20scream.%20Shea%20put%20her%20arms%20around%20me%2C%20and%20we%20laughed%20together%2C%20which%20diffused%20the%20tension.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Shea%20grew%20older%2C%20she%20came%20to%20recognize%20that%20my%20behaviors%20%E2%80%94%20like%20wariness%20around%20men%20%E2%80%94%20meant%20that%20there%20had%20to%20be%20more%20to%20my%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20was%2014%2C%20I%20told%20her%20about%20the%20assault.%20It%20came%20up%20unexpectedly%2C%20on%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20gas%20station.%20She%20was%20old%20enough%20to%20understand%20the%20fullness%20of%20the%20situation%2C%20and%20it%20would%20help%20her%20piece%20together%20who%20I%20am.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20very%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteenage-daughters-healthy-relationship-communication-snacks-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eopen%2C%20close%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20important%20to%20me%20to%20be%20transparent%20with%20her.%20My%2013-year-old%20son%2C%20however%2C%20still%20doesn't%20know%20about%20the%20assault%20%E2%80%94%20he's%20too%20young%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227ffb23a2-4da9-465c-a3e4-705d2404ab20%5C%22%3ETelling%20Shea%20about%20the%20assault%20shaped%20her%20life%2C%20too%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShea%20says%20she%20was%20completely%20heartbroken%20for%20me%20when%20she%20heard%20about%20the%20assault.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20understood%20the%20shame%20I%20carried%20about%20it%2C%20even%20though%20I%20shouldn't%20have.%20She%20told%20me%20that%20she%20never%20wanted%20me%20to%20feel%20ashamed%20and%20didn't%20want%20shame%20to%20exist%20between%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Shea%20is%2017%20and%20entering%20her%20senior%20year%20of%20high%20school.%20She%20wants%20to%20be%20an%20advocate%20for%20survivors%20of%20sexual%20assault%20and%20is%20exploring%20options%20for%20how%20to%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShea%20is%20already%20