%2F6842b3849b2a601d01b27172%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226287%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDulski%20said%20teaching%20herself%20HTML%20helped%20her%20advance%20in%20her%20career%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jennifer%20Dulski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20important%20sister%20skill%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-mckinsey-biz-rizz-networking-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelationship-building%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20you%20get%20to%20know%20your%20colleagues%20as%20human%20beings%2C%20it's%20much%20easier%20to%20adapt%20to%20big%20changes%2C%20because%20you%20have%20a%20support%20network%20within%20your%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERelationships%20can%20also%20help%20as%20you're%20climbing%20the%20ranks%20at%20a%20company.%20Early%20in%20my%20tech%20career%2C%20I%20developed%20relationships%20with%20engineers%20in%20my%20office%20because%20I%20wanted%20to%20get%20to%20know%20them.%20I%20remember%20wanting%20to%20test%20a%20hypothesis%20and%20needed%20a%20technical%20colleague%20to%20build%20a%20process%20to%20test%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20needed%20help%2C%20I%20could%20go%20to%20someone%20I%20already%20knew%20and%20ask.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20show%20executives%20what%20we%20built%20together%2C%20helping%20both%20of%20us%20advance%20our%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220fd54840-cb82-4146-8ec7-878fc722029d%5C%22%3ETake%20initiative%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20people%20early%20in%20their%20careers%20believe%20they%20need%20permission%20to%20do%20something%2C%20like%20bring%20up%20a%20big%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20successful%20people%20in%20large%20companies%20are%20what%20I%20call%20hand-raisers.%20They%20see%20things%20that%20need%20to%20be%20done%20and%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20can%20I%20help%3F%26quot%3B%20These%20people%20will%20often%20be%20given%20more%20responsibility%20faster%20because%20they%20take%20initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20my%20