s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20may%20suggest%20a%20more%20polyphenol-rich%20diet%20to%20someone%20who%20seems%20to%20have%20high%20inflammation%20and%20neuroinflammation%20based%20on%20proteomic%20test%20results%2C%20or%20may%20even%20suggest%20they%20do%20a%20little%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneurotracker-future-of-fitness-gym-strengthens-your-brain-and-body-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecognitive%20training%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20based%20on%20what%20proteomics%20says%20about%20how%20their%20brain%20is%20aging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22andrea%2C%20smiling%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66354fbcec0c696569010d4a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221798%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDr.%20Andrea%20Maier%20is%20using%20proteomics%20to%20study%20changes%20in%20her%20patients%20over%20time.%3Cp%3EChi%20Longevity%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Andrea%20Maier%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20medicine%20and%20functional%20aging%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore%2C%20told%20BI%20she%20uses%20this%20measurement%20all%20the%20time%20in%20her%20longevity%20clinics.%20For%20her%2C%20it's%20just%20a%20research%20tool%2C%20but%20if%20the%20results%20of%20her%20ongoing%20studies%20are%20decent%2C%20she%20hopes%20to%20be%20able%20to%20use%20it%20clinically%20in%20a%20few%20years'%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20know%20what%20kind%20of%20'ageotype'%20a%20person%20is%2C%20so%20what%20type%20of%20aging%20personality%20are%20you%2C%20not%20from%20a%20mental%20perspective%2C%20but%20from%20a%20physical%20perspective%2C%26quot%3B%20Maier%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20discovery%20at%20this%20moment%20in%20time%2C%20and%20at%20the%20edge%20of%20being%20clinically%20meaningful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20we%20have%20that%20validated%20tool%2C%20we%20will%20just%20add%20it%20to%20our%20routine%20testing%20and%20we%20can%20just%20tick%20the%20box%20and%20say%2C%20'I%20also%20want%20to%20know%20if%20this%20person%20is%20a%20cardiac%20ager%2C%20or%20a%20brain%20ager%2C%20or%20a%20muscle%20ager'%20because%20now%20we%20have%20a%20sensitive%20parameter%20%E2%80%94%20protein%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20be%20added%2C%26quot%3B%20Maier%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20big-name%20proteomics%20tests%20are%20Olink%20and%20SOMAscan.%20For%20now%2C%20their%20high-end%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fcell-metabolism%2Fabstract%2FS1550-4131(24)00401-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escreening%3C%2Fa%3E%20costs%20around%20%24400-%24800%20per%20patient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20losing%20lots%20of%20money%20at%20the%20moment%20because%20of%20proteomics%20for%20clinical%20research!%26quot%3B%20Maier%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221bdcf7c9-1358-4c80-adde-4dd13b082ba1%5C%22%3EProteomics%20could%20soon%20help%20predict%20who's%20most%20likely%20to%20get%20certain%20cancers%2C%20fast-tracking%20both%20prevention%20and%20treatment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20gets%20a%20breast%20ultra-sound.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fbe142f44bdb4cfa386cdb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYoung%20people%20are%20getting%20diagnosed%20with%20breast%20and%20colon%20cancer%20at%20staggering%20rates.%3Cp%3Eljubaphoto%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETop%20aging%20researchers%20at%20Stanford%20and%20Harvard%20are%20pushing%20the%20field%20forward%2C%20racing%20to%20publish%20more%20novel%20insights%20about%20the%20human%20proteome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20findings%20from%20Harvard%20aging%20researcher%20Vadim%20Gladyshev's%20lab%2C%20published%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20suggest%20that%20as%20we%20age%2C%20each%20person%20may%20even%20stand%20to%20benefit%20from%20a%20slightly%20different%20antiaging%20grocery%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20research%20this%20idea%2C%20Gladyshev%20looked%20at%20proteins%20in%20the%20blood%20of%20more%20than%2050%2C000%20people%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20all%20participants%20in%20the%20UK%20Biobank%20who%20are%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ukbiobank.ac.uk%2Fenable-your-research%2Fabout-our-data%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregularly%20tested%20and%20studied%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20their%20long-term%20health.%20He%20tracked%20their%20daily%20habits%20and%20self-reported%20routines%20like%20diet%2C%20occupation%2C%20and%20prescriptions%2C%20comparing%20those%20details%20to%20how%20each%20patient's%20organs%20were%20aging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20discovered%20some%20surprising%20connections.%20Yogurt%20eating%2C%20generally%20speaking%2C%20tended%20to%20be%20associated%20with%20better%20intestinal%20aging%20but%20had%20relatively%20no%20benefit%20to%20the%20arteries.%20White%20wine%20drinking%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20seemed%20to%20potentially%20confer%20some%20small%20benefit%20to%20the%20arteries%20while%20wreaking%20havoc%20on%20the%20gut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20main%20point%20is%20that%20people%20age%20in%20different%20ways%20in%20different%20organs%2C%20and%20therefore%20we%20need%20to%20find%20personalized%20interventions%20that%20would%20fit%20that%20particular%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20Gladyshev%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThrough%20measuring%20proteins%2C%20you%20assess%20the%20age%20of%20different%20organs%20and%20you%20say%2C%20'OK%2C%20this%20person%20is%20old%20in%20this%20artery.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20there's%20too%20much%20noise%20in%20the%20data%20to%20do%20more.%20Dr.%20Pal%20Pacher%2C%20a%20senior%20investigator%20at%20the%20National%20Institute%20on%20Alcohol%20Abuse%20and%20Alcoholism%20who%20studies%20organ%20aging%20and%20injuries%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20proteomics%20is%20simply%20not%20ready%20for%20clinical%20use%20yet.%